<p>The hot, humid summers in Music City demand reliable air conditioning systems, often running from May through September with peak usage in July and August. With average home sizes of 2,050 square feet, Nashville residents spend significantly on cooling costs, making high-efficiency HVAC systems essential for comfort and cost management. Solar panels can offset these high summer energy demands while reducing reliance on NES's grid electricity, particularly during peak cooling season when energy consumption is highest.</p>

