  <div><h3 class="font-bold">What's the best HVAC system for Nashville's climate?</h3><p>Heat pumps with SEER ratings of 16+ are ideal for Nashville's hot-humid climate, providing efficient cooling in summer and heating during mild winters. Variable-speed systems with two-stage compressors offer superior humidity control essential for comfort in Davidson County's climate. For 2,050 square foot homes, 2.5-3 ton capacity systems with smart thermostats and proper ductwork sealing provide optimal performance and energy efficiency.</p></div>
  
